Roles & Responsibilities
Job Highlights
Strong team bonding
Fast career progress
Job Description
Assist in planning and implementing marketing campaigns to drive brand awareness and growth in Singapore;
- Prepare promotional materials in various formats and channels (app, website, EDM, social media, etc.);
- Support daily operations and administration of the Marketing team;
- Conduct regular reports to analyze campaign performance and track important marketing metrics;
- Proactively collect market information and monitor industry key players;
- Handle basic media inquiry with support from the marketing manager and functional PR team;
- Perform ad-hoc marketing projects and duties as assigned.
What You'll Need
Diploma in Business Administration, Marketing or related field;
2+ years of working experience in online and offline marketing is preferred;
Experience in public relations is a plus
A good team player with strong communication skills;
Strong organizational skills and creative mindset;
Excellent command of spoken and written English and Chinese.
Energetic with a “can-do” attitude, highly self-motivated and able to work in a fast-paced, multifaceted environment;
Knowledge in different online and offline local media channels is a plus;
Proficiency in Excel, Powerpoint

